e into your own submission. You add comments that show you understand it, but never indicate the source.","position":{"start":{"line":90,"column":1},"end":{"line":90,"column":1}},"key":"wxQiACjpkj"}],"key":"vrjbqwBt5a"}],"key":"Ls5vaHr8gb"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"You find an online tutorial that walks you through the design of a schema or database and submit the resulting queries or scripts without attribution.","position":{"start":{"line":91,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"key":"ouIjZJQIqz"}],"key":"lPqXmjhZCW"}],"key":"o2TkKrqjbq"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"You use a generative model (e.g., ChatGPT) to produce your code, review it, perhaps edit it a bit, and then submit it without attribution.","position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":92,"column":1}},"key":"yNZ52J60ig"}],"key":"MHtw6CBchV"}],"key":"PovSaQ13Qd"}],"key":"D6S9azxkDH"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Consider these rules of thumb:","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"key":"ZqH90VmMuv"}],"key":"pOjyZgWyWG"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you find it efficient to use copy/paste or use a generative language model to create more than one or two lines of your query, script, or schema, you must document the original source.","position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":96